   "body" : "# SoftForks Unit\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nCurrently, there are several soft fork BIPs waiting to be deployed. A significant issue we've been facing is the uncertainty regarding deployment strategies and the inability to cleanly separate soft fork deployment from soft fork implementation.\r\n\r\n## Details\r\nCurrently we're using three mechanisms for enforcing soft forks:\r\n* BIP16 simply uses the block timestamp\r\n* BIP30 checks two specific blocks which are the only exceptions to the rule\r\n* BIP34 and BIP66 both use IsSuperMajority\r\n\r\nIn addition, VersionBits ([BIP0009](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0009.mediawiki)) proposes to add yet another mechanism that would allow us to deploy multiple soft forks simultaneously by changing the semantics of the block version field. However, this mechanism's specs are still being finalized, and it still has not been implemented.\r\n\r\nThe SoftForks unit moves all relevant logic out of consensus code in main.cpp and allows us to propose new BIPs and review them without having to commit to a particular deployment strategy. We can define the deployment strategy in softforks.cpp later without having to modify the BIPs themselves.",
